  <title>Reverse Engineering the BioNTech/Pfizer Vaccine</title>
  <dc:creator>synesis </dc:creator>
  <link>https://benjaminhan.net/posts/20201226-pfizer-vaccine-reverse-engineering/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=feed</link>
  <description><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://benjaminhan.net/posts/20201226-pfizer-vaccine-reverse-engineering/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=feed">Read on benjaminhan.net &rarr;</a></p>
 





<div class="quarto-figure quarto-figure-center">
<figure class="figure">
<p><img src="https://benjaminhan.net/posts/20201226-pfizer-vaccine-reverse-engineering/cover.jpg" class="img-fluid figure-img"></p>
<figcaption>Reverse engineering Pfizer vaccine. Image from <a href="https://berthub.eu/articles/posts/reverse-engineering-source-code-of-the-biontech-pfizer-vaccine/">Bert Hubert</a>.</figcaption>
</figure>
</div>
<p>Fascinating read about how a modern mRNA vaccine works - turns out it’s not very different from the olden days when people manually examined disassembled code (or even just binary) and tried to hack it:</p>
<ul>
<li>Life’s “magic bytes” (GA).</li>
<li>Bypassing Life’s antiviral detection.</li>
<li>Code optimization.</li>
<li>Finding the code to prop up the spike protein without an actual virus body.</li>
<li>Inflating the “counter” to prolong the usefulness of mRNA.</li>
</ul>
<p><em>Originally posted on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/benjaminhan_reverse-engineering-the-source-code-of-the-activity-6748789021054521344-cj8u">LinkedIn</a>.</em></p>



