  <dc:creator>synesis </dc:creator>
  <link>https://benjaminhan.net/posts/20201129-misinformation-overload/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=feed</link>
  <description><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://benjaminhan.net/posts/20201129-misinformation-overload/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=feed">Read on benjaminhan.net &rarr;</a></p>
 





<div class="quarto-figure quarto-figure-center">
<figure class="figure">
<p><img src="https://benjaminhan.net/posts/20201129-misinformation-overload/cover.jpg" class="img-fluid figure-img"></p>
<figcaption>Information overload. Image from <a href="https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/information-overload-helps-fake-news-spread-and-social-media-knows-it/">Scientific American</a>.</figcaption>
</figure>
</div>
<p>Insightful article from Filippo Menczer and Thomas Hills: free information leads to low-quality information.</p>
<p>Humans are not evolved to handle information overload well, and can easily fall into the traps of social herding and echo chambers. Proliferation of bots doesn’t help.</p>
